    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) headlining our lineup. His massive 14% platoon edge against a right-handed starter, paired with the favorable batting order slot and park factors, makes him our premier play. **Austin Riley** (67.79) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (67.69) follow closely behind; **Riley** leverages a significant park factor boost, while **Pasquantino** thrives on a rare, high-efficiency matchup against a right-handed starter. We are leaning heavily into these platoon-advantaged bats to maximize output, as our aggressive pursuit of stolen bases via **Corbin Carroll** and **Jose Caballero** remains a priority despite the inherent risks posed by opposing hold rates.\n\nOur bench strategy remains disciplined, with **Cole Young** (44.59) standing as the primary \"near miss.\" While **Young** offers utility, his projected efficiency fell just short of the threshold required to displace our bottom-order starters. We are prioritizing the higher ceiling of players like **Travis Bazzana** and **Alex Freeland**, who show better SP-specific adjustments today. Caution is advised regarding **Tyler Soderstrom**, whose score of 48.75 is heavily suppressed by a negative SP skill adjustment, and **Corbin Carroll**, who faces an elite hold pitcher that limits his stolen base upside today. With **Giancarlo Stanton** and **Max Muncy** still cooling their heels on the IL, we are managing our active depth carefully to avoid burning through our daily game cap reserves with lower-ceiling options.",
